The paper deals with the complexity of variants of the Satisfiability Problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves the analysis of Boolean formulas and their properties, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper's focus on monotone formulas and their restrictions suggests a connection to logic (cs.LO). Finally, the paper's analysis of the hardness of the problem implies a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves the study of computational complexity and the development of algorithms.
